---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import fs from 'node:fs';
import path from 'node:path';

// Read score files to compute per-tier stats
const runsDir = path.join(process.cwd(), 'runs');
const tierStats = { easy: { bare: [], os: [] }, medium: { bare: [], os: [] }, hard: { bare: [], os: [] } };
const tierBenchmarks = { easy: new Set(), medium: new Set(), hard: new Set() };

for (const modelDir of fs.readdirSync(runsDir)) {
  const dirPath = path.join(runsDir, modelDir);
  if (!fs.statSync(dirPath).isDirectory() || modelDir === 'control') continue;

  for (const file of fs.readdirSync(dirPath)) {
    if (!file.endsWith('.score.json')) continue;
    const score = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(path.join(dirPath, file), 'utf-8'));
    const tier = score.difficulty_tier;
    const arm = score.arm;
    if (!tier || !arm || !tierStats[tier]) continue;
    const armKey = arm === 'bare' ? 'bare' : arm === 'silent' ? 'os' : null;
    if (armKey) {
      tierStats[tier][armKey].push(score.resolved ? 1 : 0);
      tierBenchmarks[tier].add(score.benchmark);
    }
  }
}

function pct(arr: number[]): string {
  if (arr.length === 0) return '—';
  return ((arr.reduce((a, b) => a + b, 0) / arr.length) * 100).toFixed(1) + '%';
}

function delta(bare: number[], os: number[]): string {
  if (bare.length === 0 || os.length === 0) return '—';
  const b = (bare.reduce((a, c) => a + c, 0) / bare.length) * 100;
  const o = (os.reduce((a, c) => a + c, 0) / os.length) * 100;
  const d = o - b;
  return (d >= 0 ? '+' : '') + d.toFixed(1) + 'pp';
}

const articleSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "AI Debugging by Difficulty: Easy, Medium, and Hard Bug Benchmarks",
  "description": "How AI coding agents perform across easy, medium, and hard debugging tasks. Context injection helps most on medium-difficulty bugs.",
  "url": "https://needle-bench.cc/insights/difficulty-tiers/",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-30",
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "os-tack",
    "url": "https://github.com/os-tack"
  }
};
---

<Base title="AI Debugging by Difficulty: Easy, Medium, Hard — needle-bench" description="How 26 AI models perform across easy, medium, and hard real-world bugs. Context injection has the biggest effect on medium-difficulty tasks. 1,664 runs." jsonLd={articleSchema}>

  <main>
    <section class="section">
      <h1>AI Debugging by Difficulty: Easy, Medium, and Hard</h1>
      <p>needle-bench&rsquo;s 32 benchmarks are classified into three difficulty tiers based on the complexity of the underlying bug. We measured how 26 models perform across these tiers &mdash; and where context injection has the biggest impact.</p>
      <p><a href="/about/">How tiers are assigned</a> &middot; <a href="/insights/model-comparison/">Full model comparison</a></p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Overall tier performance</h2>
      <div class="data-table-wrap">
        <table class="data-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Tier</th><th>Benchmarks</th><th>Mean bare</th><th>Mean OS</th><th>Δ</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="tier easy">Easy</span></td>
              <td class="num">{tierBenchmarks.easy.size} benchmarks</td>
              <td class="num">{pct(tierStats.easy.bare)}</td>
              <td class="num">{pct(tierStats.easy.os)}</td>
              <td class="num green">{delta(tierStats.easy.bare, tierStats.easy.os)}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="tier medium">Medium</span></td>
              <td class="num">{tierBenchmarks.medium.size} benchmarks</td>
              <td class="num">{pct(tierStats.medium.bare)}</td>
              <td class="num">{pct(tierStats.medium.os)}</td>
              <td class="num green">{delta(tierStats.medium.bare, tierStats.medium.os)}</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="tier hard">Hard</span></td>
              <td class="num">{tierBenchmarks.hard.size} benchmarks</td>
              <td class="num">{pct(tierStats.hard.bare)}</td>
              <td class="num">{pct(tierStats.hard.os)}</td>
              <td class="num green">{delta(tierStats.hard.bare, tierStats.hard.os)}</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <p class="muted">Data computed at build time from {tierBenchmarks.easy.size + tierBenchmarks.medium.size + tierBenchmarks.hard.size} benchmarks across 26 models.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>What makes a bug &ldquo;hard&rdquo;?</h2>
      <p>Difficulty tiers are assigned by the benchmark author based on the bug&rsquo;s characteristics:</p>
      <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        <li><strong>Easy</strong> &mdash; single-file bugs with clear error messages. An off-by-one, a wrong variable name, a missing null check. The test failure points directly at the problem.</li>
        <li><strong>Medium</strong> &mdash; multi-file bugs or bugs where the error message is misleading. Requires understanding how components interact. Schema drifts, configuration mismatches, race conditions with clear symptoms.</li>
        <li><strong>Hard</strong> &mdash; bugs that require deep domain knowledge or produce symptoms far from their root cause. Silent data corruption, split-brain consensus failures, timing-dependent security issues. The test fails, but the failure tells you almost nothing about where to look.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>The medium-tier sweet spot</h2>
      <p>Context injection has its largest effect on medium-difficulty bugs. This makes intuitive sense:</p>
      <ul style="padding-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem;">
        <li><strong>Easy bugs</strong>: most models solve these bare. The error message is enough. Context helps, but baseline is already high.</li>
        <li><strong>Medium bugs</strong>: the agent needs to understand project structure to find the right files. Context injection provides exactly this &mdash; file tree, test output, recent changes. The agent skips 5&ndash;10 exploration turns and starts debugging immediately.</li>
        <li><strong>Hard bugs</strong>: even with context, these require reasoning about non-obvious causality. Context helps (the agent knows <em>where</em> to look) but the fix requires domain insight that context alone can&rsquo;t provide.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>If you&rsquo;re deciding whether to invest in context injection for your workflow, medium-complexity tasks are where you&rsquo;ll see the biggest return.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Tier-specific model recommendations</h2>
      <div class="data-table-wrap">
        <table class="data-table">
          <thead>
            <tr><th>Task difficulty</th><th>Recommendation</th><th>Why</th></tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="tier easy">Easy</span></td>
              <td>Budget model + context</td>
              <td>Haiku 4.5 + context hits 90.6%. No need for frontier models on easy bugs.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="tier medium">Medium</span></td>
              <td>Mid-tier model + context</td>
              <td>GPT-4o or Gemini Flash + context reach 65&ndash;81%. Context is the multiplier.</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td><span class="tier hard">Hard</span></td>
              <td>Frontier model + context</td>
              <td>Opus 4 or DeepSeek R1. Hard bugs need reasoning power <em>and</em> context.</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2>Key takeaways</h2>
      <ol style="padding-left: 1.5rem; line-height: 1.8;">
        <li><strong>Context injection has the biggest ROI on medium-difficulty bugs</strong> &mdash; the most common category in real codebases.</li>
        <li><strong>Easy bugs don&rsquo;t need frontier models.</strong> Save your token budget for hard problems.</li>
        <li><strong>Hard bugs need both reasoning and context.</strong> Neither alone is sufficient for the hardest tier.</li>
        <li><strong>Match model cost to task difficulty.</strong> A tiered approach (budget for easy, mid for medium, frontier for hard) optimizes both cost and resolve rate.</li>
      </ol>
      <p style="margin-top: 1.5rem;"><a href="/insights/model-comparison/">Full model comparison</a> &middot; <a href="/insights/open-vs-closed/">Open vs closed models</a> &middot; <a href="https://ostk.ai/insights/context-injection/">Context injection deep dive</a></p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .data-table-wrap {
    overflow-x: auto;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .data-table {
    width: 100%;
    border-collapse: collapse;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
  }

  .data-table th,
  .data-table td {
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
    text-align: left;
  }

  .data-table th {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }

  .data-table .num {
    text-align: right;
    font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  }

  .data-table .green {
    color: var(--green);
  }

  .tier {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.15em 0.5em;
    border-radius: 3px;
  }

  .tier.easy { color: var(--green); background: rgba(63, 185, 80, 0.1); }
  .tier.medium { color: #d29922; background: rgba(210, 153, 34, 0.1); }
  .tier.hard { color: var(--red); background: rgba(248, 81, 73, 0.1); }

  .card {
    background: var(--surface);
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    border-radius: 6px;
    padding: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    overflow-x: auto;
  }

  .card pre {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.5;
  }

  ol li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }
</style>
